==Abstract==

This IIP describes the Secure Multisig Setup (SMS) protocol adapted for INTcoin's ML-DSA-87 signatures. It implements BIP 128/129 concepts for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Setting up multisig wallets requires secure exchange of extended public keys between participants. SMS provides:
* Encrypted key exchange
* Verification of all participants
* Standardized descriptor generation

==Specification==

===Roles===

* '''Coordinator''': Initiates setup, collects keys, generates descriptor
* '''Signers''': Provide extended public keys, verify final descriptor

===Protocol Flow===

# Coordinator creates session with M-of-N parameters
# Coordinator generates session token
# Each signer exports their key record (encrypted with token)
# Coordinator collects all key records
# Coordinator generates multisig descriptor
# All signers verify the descriptor derives expected addresses

===Session Token===

<pre>
token = Base58Check(random_bytes(20))
</pre>

===Key Record Format===

<pre>
Version: 1.0
Token: <session_token>
Key: <extended_public_key>
Derivation: m/48'/2210'/0'/2'
Fingerprint: <master_fingerprint>
</pre>

===Encryption===

Key records are encrypted with the session token:
<pre>
encrypted = ChaCha20-Poly1305(
    key = SHA3-256(token),
    nonce = random(12),
    plaintext = key_record
)
</pre>

===Descriptor Generation===

The coordinator generates a descriptor in the format:
<pre>
wsh(sortedmulti(M, [fp1/48'/2210'/0'/2']xpub1/0/*, [fp2/...]xpub2/0/*, ...))
</pre>

===Verification===

All signers MUST verify:
# Their key is included correctly
# First address matches expected value
# M and N parameters are correct

===INTcoin Adaptations===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Component !! BIP 129 !! IIP-28
|-
| Extended keys || xpub/xprv || ixpub/ixprv
|-
| Key size || ~111 chars || ~3600 chars
|-
| Signature scheme || ECDSA || ML-DSA-87
|-
| Coin type || varies || 2210
|}

